-- Chile Government Expects Cabinet Change by November, Emol Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-09-18T15:45:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-18/chile-government-expects-cabinet-change-by-november-emol-says.html
Chilean President Sebastian Pinera
may have to shuffle his Cabinet after the resignations of at
least two ministers by November to run for Congress or start
campaigning for the 2013 presidential election, Santiago-based
newspaper  El Mercurio ’s online edition Emol  reported today ,
citing Labor Minister Evelyn Matthei.  Public Works Minister  Laurence Golborne , who led the rescue
of 33 trapped miners in 2010, and Defense Minister Andres Allamand are possible candidates to replace Pinera when he is
scheduled to leave office in March 2014, the newspaper reported,
citing unidentified officials it didn’t name.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
